    {
      "title": "Negation with kāore",
      "level": "A1",
      "function": "Say what is not so",
      "source": "contributor",
      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 9,
      "explanation": "Kāore starts the negative and the subject moves forward: Kei te mōhio au → Kāore au i te mōhio (I don't know). Past uses i: Kāore ia i haere mai (she didn't come). 'There is no…' is kāore he…: Kāore he kai (there's no food).",
      "culture_note": "",
      "references": [
        {
          "title": "Wikipedia: Māori language — grammar",
          "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M%C4%81ori_language"
        },
        {
