      "reviewed": true,
      "display_order": 10,
      "explanation": "Question words slot into the sentence types you already know: He aha tēnei? (What is this?), Ko wai tō ingoa? (Who/what is your name?), Kei hea…? (Where is…?), Nō hea koe? (Where are you from?), E hia…? (How many?).",
      "culture_note": "Nō hea koe? — where are you from — is often the first real question in a Māori conversation; whakapapa (origins) matter.",
      "references": [
